Footballers throughout the Premier League are today wearing special rainbow coloured laces to support Stonewall and Paddy Power's anti-homophobia campaign.

Arsenal already demonstrated their support for the issue in a television advert, and now they, as well as players from around the Premier League, can be seen wearing the laces in today's fixtures.

Mikel Arteta, Per Mertesacker, Alex Oxlade-Chamberlain and Lukas Podolski are just some of the names involved at The Emirates.

