An FA statement on the campaign read: 'Like that of the Rainbow Laces campaign, The FA's message is simple: homophobia, like all forms of discrimination, is unacceptable.' 

Joey Barton is another advocate of the cause. The QPR midfielder told The Metro: 'There are always people who are going to complain – they will say blue is red for the sake of an argument.

'The key is getting the message out to the public that us lads are supportive of fellow pros and supporters, no matter what their sexual orientation.' 

