Speaking about the campaign to Arsenal.com, Arsene Wenger said: 'The sport is taking responsibility so perhaps our sport can be ahead of the trend in society. 

'In this aspect I don't think we are but at least we support it and I think it's important.

'I believe that we have a responsibility because people look at our game and see what kind of values we support. The fight against homophobia and any discrimination is very important and we have that responsibility.

